# kanshi -- display hotplug / multi-monitor arrangement. Started by river
# (autostart in base). Reacts to outputs being plugged/unplugged and
# applies the first profile whose output set matches what's connected.
#
# SHARED BASE + PER-HOST PROFILES: this file only pulls in the per-host
# profile files. Each machine's profiles are keyed by that machine's
# actual output names, so only the current host's profiles ever match --
# and an unconfigured machine simply has no matching profile, leaving
# river's default arrangement untouched (graceful, no hard failure).
#
# Profiles handle the "enable external displays when present/hotplugged"
# requirement automatically: plugging a monitor changes the connected
# output set, kanshi switches to the matching (docked/external) profile.
#
# Turning the internal panel off *on lid close* is NOT done here -- kanshi
# can't see lid state, only which outputs are connected. The river-lid
# helper (per-host) handles that.
#
# The include path is relative to this file's directory (~/.config/kanshi)
# and matches only real per-host files placed directly in hosts/. The
# template and example profiles live in hosts/examples/ (a subdirectory the
# "hosts/*.conf" glob does NOT descend into), so they are never loaded and
# can't accidentally match a machine you haven't configured yet.
include "hosts/*.conf"
